Reasoning: The paper deals with the reconfiguration problem of graph colourings, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The problem involves finding a sequence of proper colourings that differ on exactly one vertex, which is related to shortest path algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also includes discussions on polynomial-time solvability and fixed-parameter tractability, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG).
